# Copy to .env and fill in.
# All variables are OPTIONAL. The template runs out-of-the-box with sensible defaults.

# ─── HTTP / TLS (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When both are set, the HTTP server can be started over HTTPS by your main.ts.
# When unset, plain HTTP is used.
# TLS_CERT_PATH=/etc/ssl/certs/server.crt
# TLS_KEY_PATH=/etc/ssl/private/server.key

# ─── SMTP (optional — used by SmtpEmailAdapter.createFromEnv) ─────────────────
# When SMTP_HOST and SMTP_FROM_ADDRESS are not set, createFromEnv returns
# undefined and you should fall back to ConsoleEmailAdapter.
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.example.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=false
# SMTP_USER=apikey-user
# SMTP_PASS=apikey-secret
# SMTP_FROM_ADDRESS=noreply@example.com
# SMTP_FROM_NAME=My App

# ─── Logging ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ConsoleLogger writes JSON to stdout. No env vars required — every log line
# automatically includes the per-request correlationId when one is active.
